title: Janet Jackson Debuts Dance-Filled 'BURNITUP!' Lyric Video Ft. Missy Elliott
text:
Comments The singer hires her DJ, dancers, crew members and some fans in the crowd for the fun clip filmed during her 'Unbreakable' tour. 
Janet Jackson wants the world to sing along to her "BURNITUP!" to help her celebrate the release of her " Unbreakable " album. On Friday, October 2, the day her comeback effort officially arrived, the diva shared a lyric video for her collaboration with Missy Elliott . Arriving via Jackson's YouTube channel, the video is made up of scenes filmed during the songbird's "Unbreakable" tour. In between shots of her performing onstage, lyrics of the song are found on the signs held by her DJ, dancers, crew members and some fans in the crowd. "BURNITUP!" was first debuted live by Jackson as she kicked off her tour a few weeks ago. The song appears alongside "No Sleeep" and "Unbreakable" on her just-released album. Marking her first full-length in seven years, it has been receiving positive reviews from critics. In other Jackson news, she was recently forced to cancel two Las Vegas shows on her tour as she needed to rest her vocal chords. Originally scheduled to take place at Planet Hollywood's Axis theater later this month, the concerts have been rescheduled for May 14, 2016 at a different venue at the MGM Grand Garden.
